Glassbox is an art collective founded in 1997 in Paris and made up of artists, whose objective is to promote contemporary creation in the field of visual arts.
Panteón Rococó is a Mexican rock band from Mexico City.

The Eiffel Tower (/ˈaɪfəl/ ⓘ EYE-fəl; French: Tour Eiffel  ⓘ) is a wrought-iron lattice tower on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. It is named after the engineer Gustave Eiffel, whose company designed and built the tower from 1887 to 1889.
Cour Saint-Émilion is a private road in the Bercy district in the 12th arrondissement of Paris.

Chinese house churches are unregistered and more or less clandestine Christian house churches in China. Among them, there are many evangelical churches. In 2010, the Pew Research Center estimated that there were 35 million Protestant Christians in China (or 60% of Chinese Protestants) and 3.3 million Catholic Christians (or 37% of Chinese Catholics) who participated in house churches.
Sainte-Marie de Valmagne Abbey is a Cistercian abbey located in Villeveyrac, in the French department of Hérault in the Occitanie region.
Several chapels of the Catholic Church are called Sainte-Bernadette chapel in reference to Saint Bernadette Soubirous in France:
The Bagatelle rose garden, located in the Bagatelle park in the Bois de Boulogne (Paris) is one of the most important and oldest rose gardens in France.

The Church of Saint-François-d'Assise (in Dutch: Sint-Franciscuskerk) is a religious building in the neo-Gothic style located on Rue des Palais, in Schaerbeek (Brussels). Built in the 19th century as the church of the Récollets convent, it was damaged during the Second World War. Rebuilt in 1947 it became a parish in 1961 when the Récollets fathers left the premises. Since 2006 – and under the name of Saint-Nicolas-de-Myre church – it has been a place of worship of the Romanian Orthodox Church.

The Bois de Boulogne (French le bois de Boulogne) is a city park in Paris. Covering an area of ​​8.5 km², it is located in the 16th arrondissement between the suburbs of Boulogne-Billancourt and Neuilly-sur-Seine.
Rose bushes under the trees is a painting created by the Austrian painter Gustav Klimt around 1905. This oil painting on canvas is a landscape representing trees under which we can see rose bushes.

Porte d'Ivry is one of the gates of Paris, France, located in the Gare district of the 13th arrondissement. It separates Paris from Ivry-sur-Seine in Val-de-Marne. Historically, it is one of the 17 gates opened in the walls of Thiers in the middle of the 19th century to protect the capital.

The Petite Ceinture de Paris line, commonly referred to as the "Petite Ceinture", is a 32 kilometer long double-track railway line encircling Paris within the Boulevards des Maréchaux. Although still part of the national rail network, it is today unused for most of its route.

An impulse phobia or intrusive thought is a medical symptom characterized by the obsessive fear of committing a criminal, transgressive, or dangerous act for oneself or others. It can be one of the symptoms of obsessive compulsive disorder (OCD).
Mylène Farmer, whose real name is Mylène Gautier, is a French singer-songwriter, producer, illustrator and actress, born September 12, 1961 in Montreal (Quebec).
The Square des Anciens-Combattants-d’Indochine is a green space in the 12th arrondissement of Paris located in the Porte Dorée district.

Ateliers Perrault Frères is a carpentry, carpentry, ironwork and artistic locksmithing company, founded in 1760 and, today, specialized in the restoration of heritage buildings, the creation of traditional creations and the reproduction of works of art from the 14th century to the 20th century. They are the heirs of ancestral know-how which allows them to master these different trades.
The Ranelagh Garden is a green space in the 16th arrondissement of Paris, France.
Franciscan monks founded numerous monasteries or convents, known in French-speaking countries as Cordeliers convents.

Scientology is a set of beliefs and practices whose principles were developed in the United States in 1952 by L. Ron Hubbard. The Church of Scientology was founded in Camden, New Jersey and opened in December 1953.

Hippocrene is a spring located on Mount Helicon, Greece, near Thespiae. It is known for its important presence in Greek mythology as the source of the Muses and for the story of its creation linked to the myth of the winged horse Pegasus. Poets come to this source to seek inspiration.

Nuit Blanche (French pronunciation: ) (Sleepless Night) is an annual all-night or night-time arts festival of a city. A Nuit Blanche typically has museums, private and public art galleries, and other cultural institutions open and free of charge, with the centre of the city itself being turned into a de facto art gallery, providing space for art installations, performances (music, film, dance, performance art), themed social gatherings, and other activities.

Futebol Clube do Porto, more commonly abbreviated to FC Porto, is a Portuguese multi-sports club in the city of Porto, founded in 1893. Its football section has participated in all editions of the Portuguese championship of which it is a founding member, since 1934. It shares this characteristic with Benfica Lisbon and Sporting CP, two Lisbon clubs with which it forms Os Três Grandes in French: "The big three".
Rue des Bourdonnais is a street in the 1st arrondissement of Paris, France.

Notre-Dame-du-Rosaire (French pronunciation: ) is a municipality of about 400 people in Montmagny Regional County Municipality within the Chaudière-Appalaches region of Quebec, Canada. It is located on the south shore of the St. Lawrence River, 20 kilometres (12 mi) south of Montmagny on Route 283.
